You  could either  look for  a package  called "NetPBM",  available on
Aminet, or use  Photogenics 4; I know the latter  has support for PPM,
since I wrote the PPM module ;)

Note however, that PPM  is not a 32 bit format, it  can only handle 24
bits (red, green,  blue, no alpha). The only  format with decent alpha
support I have  come across until now is PNG, but  that's a bit harder
to read. There is a very basic PNG reader in the Engine demo, but that
one cannot handle everything, and uses libpng... 

